WEBVTT

00:17.208 --> 00:19.499
Although inspired by the life
of Bruno Sulak,

00:19.500 --> 00:20.707
this film is fiction.

00:20.708 --> 00:24.124
Characters, situations, places
and certain events

00:24.125 --> 00:26.999
might be modified or reinvented

00:27.000 --> 00:28.791
to express the author's artistic vision.

02:11.541 --> 02:14.250
Ladies and gentlemen, nobody move.
This is a robbery.

02:14.958 --> 02:17.874
No one will get hurt if you do as I say.

02:17.875 --> 02:19.415
Tie your hands.

02:19.416 --> 02:22.082
- I have two kids.
- You can tell that to the cops.

02:22.083 --> 02:23.499
The tape.

02:23.500 --> 02:26.582
Open the cash drawers slowly.

02:26.583 --> 02:27.957
Fill up the bag.

02:27.958 --> 02:30.332
Fill up the bag that has been provided.

02:30.333 --> 02:34.083
The checkout at the far end, get the bills
together and give them to number 2.

02:34.791 --> 02:38.208
Morning, ma'am. I'm gonna take a lollipop.

02:40.416 --> 02:42.791
Here. Tie your hands, sit down.

02:46.083 --> 02:48.083
And remember, this money is not yours.

02:48.208 --> 02:51.415
- Hurry up. Do as he says.
- Thank you, Nicole.

02:51.416 --> 02:53.332
Relax, it's not your money.

02:53.333 --> 02:56.333
- Checks as well?
- Yes, checks and bills, thank you.

02:57.125 --> 02:59.207
Good. There.

02:59.208 --> 03:02.166
It's easy, right? Thank you.
Have a lovely day.

03:02.416 --> 03:04.707
- Here.
- Thank you.

03:04.708 --> 03:06.416
Thank you, ma'am.

03:07.625 --> 03:09.875
Can you hold this? It's too sweet.

03:11.250 --> 03:15.165
Have a pleasant day.
Apologies for the inconvenience.

03:15.166 --> 03:17.250
And I'll see you soon.

04:11.791 --> 04:12.625
Hey!

04:14.333 --> 04:17.000
Careful. Watch the road, Annie.

04:32.916 --> 04:36.291
- So this isn't your bag?
- No.

04:38.166 --> 04:40.665
And what's in it is not yours either?

04:40.666 --> 04:42.000
No, it's not.

04:42.500 --> 04:44.083
What are you doing here, then?

04:45.333 --> 04:47.166
- I don't know.
- Well, you're innocent.

04:48.916 --> 04:51.957
Damn. That was very nearly
a miscarriage of justice.

04:51.958 --> 04:53.957
I was this close to sending him to prison.

04:53.958 --> 04:57.332
Excuse me. Sorry.
I'm sorry. You can go.

04:57.333 --> 04:59.290
I'm sorry.

04:59.291 --> 05:01.250
Wait, Tonio, tell me one thing.

05:01.791 --> 05:03.541
How many times have I arrested you?

05:03.916 --> 05:06.999
- Give me a number.
- I don't know.

05:07.000 --> 05:09.665
Six... Maybe seven times.

05:09.666 --> 05:11.583
Seventeen times.

05:12.125 --> 05:13.208
Sit down.

05:17.291 --> 05:19.582
Come on, the old lady recognized you.

05:19.583 --> 05:22.041
Boss, there's been a robbery
at the Orange Continent.

05:22.958 --> 05:25.249
- The Orange Continent?
- The old Unico.

05:25.250 --> 05:27.749
- Shit. Any casualties?
- None.

05:27.750 --> 05:29.290
Well, that's something.

05:29.291 --> 05:30.624
How much?

05:30.625 --> 05:32.915
Around 200k. This week's takings.

05:32.916 --> 05:35.249
We've identified one of the guys
from a photo.

05:35.250 --> 05:39.874
Sulak Bruno, born on November 6th, '55,
in Sidi Bel Abbès, Algeria.

05:39.875 --> 05:43.040
Legionnaire in the 2nd REP,
deserted 18 months ago.

05:43.041 --> 05:44.458
Does he have a record?

05:44.583 --> 05:48.124
He did four months for theft
when he was 18.

05:48.125 --> 05:50.124
Small stuff.

05:50.125 --> 05:53.582
Since he deserted,
he's upgraded his business,

05:53.583 --> 05:55.458
he's suspected in a dozen robberies.

05:55.708 --> 05:59.040
Always supermarkets.
Avignon, Albi, Beaune.

05:59.041 --> 06:02.208
Always the same crew. Two of them,
plus one who waits in the car.

06:03.416 --> 06:05.457
- Who identified him?
- Two employees.

06:05.458 --> 06:06.957
They were in the robbery.

06:06.958 --> 06:10.666
- They're here.
- Could they be accomplices?

06:11.583 --> 06:14.791
Honestly, everything's possible,
but I doubt it.

06:16.458 --> 06:18.665
- Bring them in. I'll talk to them.
- Okay.

06:18.666 --> 06:20.833
- No, leave the photo here.
- Okay.

06:22.833 --> 06:24.375
Tonio, my boy.

06:24.708 --> 06:28.000
This is your lucky day.
Get out of here, I'm tired of you.

06:29.458 --> 06:31.541
Just go before I change my mind.

06:35.333 --> 06:37.666
The black and white doesn't help.

06:37.791 --> 06:40.375
You can't see the color of his eyes.

06:41.958 --> 06:44.374
- It's a bit stiff.
- But mugshots, you know...

06:44.375 --> 06:46.000
No one looks great in profile.

06:46.416 --> 06:48.874
He's better looking in person.

06:48.875 --> 06:52.000
Eyes like that are really unforgettable.

06:53.916 --> 06:56.374
And his smile. A big smile.

06:56.375 --> 06:58.208
- Lovely.
- A handsome boy.

07:00.500 --> 07:01.832
And polite.

07:01.833 --> 07:04.040
Good-looking.

07:04.041 --> 07:05.833
Really good-looking.

07:08.416 --> 07:09.916
Wait, ladies,

07:10.791 --> 07:13.499
we're talking about a robber.
Not some pretty boy in a club.

07:13.500 --> 07:15.790
Your little angel has stolen 20 million.

07:15.791 --> 07:16.999
Yes, well, I...

07:17.000 --> 07:19.874
- And the other?
- The other?

07:19.875 --> 07:22.000
- What other?
- The other guy.

07:23.666 --> 07:25.707
I couldn't really see.

07:25.708 --> 07:29.124
- I didn't pay attention, sorry.
- Me neither.

07:29.125 --> 07:31.000
Thank you, ladies.

07:53.125 --> 07:54.916
Who is this clown?

07:59.666 --> 08:01.250
- One.
- What?

08:02.541 --> 08:03.832
Forget it.

08:03.833 --> 08:05.499
I don't believe you, you won't do it.

08:05.500 --> 08:07.332
- Two.
- Stop it.

08:07.333 --> 08:10.041
It's stupid,
we don't even know how deep it is.

08:10.791 --> 08:12.125
Bruno.

08:13.708 --> 08:16.749
- I'm serious. Very serious.
- You're very serious?

08:16.750 --> 08:19.332
If you do this, I won't talk to you
for the rest of the day.

08:19.333 --> 08:21.916
- The rest of the day? That's a long time.
- Very long.

08:25.916 --> 08:27.458
- Three.
- Bruno, stop.

08:29.416 --> 08:31.416
I'm serious. I'm scared.

08:32.458 --> 08:33.999
I love you too.

08:34.000 --> 08:35.500
No!

08:44.416 --> 08:45.958
Yeah, right.

08:47.416 --> 08:49.041
Very funny.

08:54.250 --> 08:56.541
Come up now.

08:57.791 --> 08:59.291
Bruno!

09:14.500 --> 09:15.958
Bruno!

09:21.875 --> 09:23.125
Bruno!

09:24.000 --> 09:25.916
You're a dick!

09:27.208 --> 09:28.833
Fuck!

09:32.166 --> 09:33.957
You're a dick.

09:33.958 --> 09:35.707
I... You scared me.

09:35.708 --> 09:37.624
You're as crazy as I am.

09:37.625 --> 09:39.291
You didn't know that?

10:08.875 --> 10:10.707
Do you know what I love the most?

10:10.708 --> 10:12.000
Besides me?

10:13.541 --> 10:15.166
Besides you.

10:19.125 --> 10:20.999
<i>The wind on the skin.</i>

10:21.000 --> 10:22.416
<i>The wind that caresses.</i>

10:32.375 --> 10:33.915
<i>And you?</i>

10:33.916 --> 10:35.916
<i>- Besides you?
- Yes.</i>

10:37.375 --> 10:38.750
The speed.

10:44.416 --> 10:46.957
<i>Do you know what I wanted to do
when I was young?</i>

10:46.958 --> 10:49.416
<i>- No.
- A lot of things.</i>

10:52.583 --> 10:55.291
- What's stopping you?
- Nothing.

10:56.708 --> 10:58.125
I'll do them all one day.

10:58.708 --> 11:01.082
<i>- Do you know what I like the most?
- No.</i>

11:01.083 --> 11:05.374
<i>When the sky and the sea meet
and you can't see the horizon.</i>

11:05.375 --> 11:07.625
We'll go live by the sea.

11:09.416 --> 11:10.625
<i>And we'll have a baby.</i>

11:11.125 --> 11:12.291
What?

11:48.958 --> 11:51.665
- Hi. I'm Bruno.
- Annie, nice to meet you.

11:51.666 --> 11:53.083
Nice to meet you.

11:57.333 --> 11:58.957
We can share a bottle.

11:58.958 --> 12:00.916
Sounds good. Who's that?

12:03.458 --> 12:05.750
- Wow.
- Marika's here.

12:07.916 --> 12:09.415
Look at my princess.

12:09.416 --> 12:12.249
- I thought you were coming tonight.
- Hi!

12:12.250 --> 12:14.832
- Nope.
- Oh, wow.

12:14.833 --> 12:16.625
- How are you?
- My princess.

12:19.666 --> 12:20.750
Come have a drink.

12:21.208 --> 12:23.166
This is beautiful.
I'm happy to see you.

12:23.583 --> 12:27.207
- What do you think of the view?
- It's not too bad.

12:27.208 --> 12:29.416
Over there is <i>Le Château de ma mère.</i>

12:29.708 --> 12:31.625
And over there, <i>La Gloire de mon père.</i>

12:31.791 --> 12:34.000
And he just jumped on him.

12:34.708 --> 12:36.124
On his shoulders.

12:36.125 --> 12:39.416
And he just bit his neck.

12:39.958 --> 12:43.207
Seriously. His tendons were...

12:43.208 --> 12:46.415
- That's not what happened.
- Yes, it is.

12:46.416 --> 12:48.499
You can't say that, Bruno.

12:48.500 --> 12:50.874
It's a matter of common sense.

12:50.875 --> 12:54.165
You have no common sense.
You can't say that politics is useless.

12:54.166 --> 12:56.749
Politics only helps the rich to stay rich,

12:56.750 --> 12:59.040
and the poor have to shut up.

12:59.041 --> 13:02.124
You're exhausting,
you don't believe in anything.

13:02.125 --> 13:04.374
I believe in freedom.

13:04.375 --> 13:07.082
And Chirac, Marchais
and Mitterrand won't give it to us.

13:07.083 --> 13:08.000
I disagree.

13:08.708 --> 13:11.707
- Who's taking the second share?
- You.

13:11.708 --> 13:14.457
But my share is your share.

13:14.458 --> 13:16.707
Everybody did the job,
everybody gets paid.

13:16.708 --> 13:18.833
I don't care, I don't want it.

13:20.166 --> 13:22.208
Give me the checks.

13:25.375 --> 13:26.833
Can you believe it?

13:27.208 --> 13:31.708
We've given a lot of groceries
to a lot of good people.

13:32.625 --> 13:34.790
But we should tell these good people,

13:34.791 --> 13:37.874
because instead of thanking you,
they want to see you in jail.

13:37.875 --> 13:40.624
- Robin Hood.
- We haven't done anything wrong.

13:40.625 --> 13:42.958
Except stealing from
bigger thieves than us.

13:43.333 --> 13:46.124
Don't worry,
the big cats never go to jail.

13:46.125 --> 13:48.832
- Communist!
- It's not about that,

13:48.833 --> 13:50.666
I just want to blow everything up.

13:51.416 --> 13:52.541
Terrorist, then.

13:54.583 --> 13:57.208
- Are you messing with me?
- No.

13:58.916 --> 14:00.416
What?

14:01.833 --> 14:03.249
Nothing.

14:03.250 --> 14:05.041
You're handsome.

14:22.333 --> 14:27.291
Ladies and gentlemen, nobody move.
This is a robbery.

14:29.208 --> 14:31.375
Do as I say and everything will be fine.

14:36.000 --> 14:37.375
Hurry up!

15:08.791 --> 15:10.207
SUPERMARKET COOP

15:10.208 --> 15:12.500
Nobody move, this is a robbery!

15:14.000 --> 15:17.457
Do as I say, and no one will get hurt.

15:17.458 --> 15:19.249
Open the cash drawers.

15:19.250 --> 15:22.000
Empty them in this bag. Hello, ma'am.

15:34.250 --> 15:37.333
The 500 bills together,
the 100 bills together.

15:58.250 --> 16:00.333
- Come on, baby.
- You have to put it behind.

16:00.875 --> 16:02.625
Look.

16:03.208 --> 16:05.166
- Amazing.
- You got me closer.

16:06.791 --> 16:08.750
- That's our ball.
- That's two points.

16:09.958 --> 16:12.000
Should we start again?

16:18.083 --> 16:20.666
<i>- Hola, cabrones!</i>
- Patrick.

16:22.375 --> 16:24.375
Behind the mountain.

16:26.083 --> 16:27.415
You're not ready to play now.

16:27.416 --> 16:30.165
- I'm exhausted.
- It's nice to see you.

16:30.166 --> 16:31.500
What do we have to drink?

16:32.000 --> 16:35.957
Some friends of mine had a vineyard,
amazing wines.

16:35.958 --> 16:39.540
They could mess with your head.

16:39.541 --> 16:42.833
But apparently,
it was back in the 12th, 13th century.

16:42.958 --> 16:45.665
- Wines that drive you mad?
- Or blind.

16:45.666 --> 16:48.707
That's totally bullshit.

16:48.708 --> 16:52.082
- It doesn't happen with all the grapes.
- You said that.

16:52.083 --> 16:54.332
- Okay, I'm going back up.
- What?

16:54.333 --> 16:56.165
- Yeah.
- Are you coming with me?

16:56.166 --> 16:58.165
- Are you coming?
- I'll be right there.

16:58.166 --> 17:01.665
- Be careful.
- Don't worry, I worked in a restaurant.

17:01.666 --> 17:04.040
Put the knife down.

17:04.041 --> 17:07.124
- You're trying to calm me down.
- Calm down.

17:07.125 --> 17:11.457
You're trying to calm me down, I know you.

17:11.458 --> 17:13.291
I know you.

17:14.625 --> 17:16.333
This feels nice.

17:16.916 --> 17:19.790
Patrick, listen to me if you want to come.

17:19.791 --> 17:22.290
Why not that one? It's closer.

17:22.291 --> 17:25.041
No. We've already hit
all the supermarkets in the area.

17:25.166 --> 17:27.874
No, we haven't done that one,
outside Rodez.

17:27.875 --> 17:30.040
Which one is it? Continent, Mammouth?

17:30.041 --> 17:33.624
My dear Continent lover, it's a Mammouth.

17:33.625 --> 17:37.707
Patrick, you go in after me,
you hold the cashiers at bay.

17:37.708 --> 17:40.749
- And where am I, Bruno?
- You, my love,

17:40.750 --> 17:44.082
you're in the parking lot,
ready, engine going.

17:44.083 --> 17:45.833
Okay. What kind of car do we have?

17:45.958 --> 17:49.040
- A Renault 30.
- No, I said I wanted a BMW.

17:49.041 --> 17:51.374
- It's fine.
- They're heavy, not reliable.

17:51.375 --> 17:53.207
We tried to get another one.

17:53.208 --> 17:55.290
I want a BMW, guys.

17:55.291 --> 17:57.749
It's about the driver, not the car.

17:57.750 --> 18:00.915
- Is everybody ready?
- Ready.

18:00.916 --> 18:03.499
- No worries.
- We'll go at six o'clock tomorrow morning.

18:03.500 --> 18:05.958
- Don't party too hard.
- You too, Pat.

18:07.958 --> 18:11.708
I'll check the plan one more time.

18:11.833 --> 18:14.750
Okay, let's go. Good night, everyone.

18:16.708 --> 18:18.625
Just in case...

18:38.250 --> 18:40.790
Give the bag to the next cashier.

18:40.791 --> 18:42.833
Come on, it'll be over soon.

18:46.083 --> 18:47.832
Fill it.

18:47.833 --> 18:51.165
Next register, thank you.
Please stay calm.

18:51.166 --> 18:53.249
- What are you doing?
- Fill up the bag.

18:53.250 --> 18:56.415
- You coon, you're not Al Capone.
- I'll show you.

18:56.416 --> 18:59.166
- What's up?
- Patrick, cable ties, go on.

18:59.875 --> 19:03.165
- What do I do?
- Cable ties!

19:03.166 --> 19:06.374
Everybody stay calm.
Nobody moves, hands on the counter.

19:06.375 --> 19:08.207
I don't want to die, I have a little girl.

19:08.208 --> 19:09.707
Shut up. On the counter.

19:09.708 --> 19:12.875
- Load it. Shut up.
- You'll pay for this.

19:14.583 --> 19:15.749
- Load it.
- Drago?

19:15.750 --> 19:16.750
Fill up the bag!

19:18.250 --> 19:19.832
Hands on the counter!

19:19.833 --> 19:21.165
Listen to me, fuck!

19:21.166 --> 19:22.124
I said shut up!

19:22.125 --> 19:23.875
- What's wrong? You got this?
- We're fine.

19:24.000 --> 19:24.875
- Tell me.
- We're fine.

19:28.500 --> 19:31.958
You're not going to die, calm down.
Nothing will happen. Relax!

19:33.041 --> 19:34.625
Get your hands off me. Relax.

19:35.875 --> 19:37.707
Shut up, stop moving!

19:37.708 --> 19:39.540
Stop moving!

19:39.541 --> 19:41.707
- Are you insane?
- Move.

19:41.708 --> 19:44.165
- Listen to me! Calm down.
- I don't want to die.

19:44.166 --> 19:47.500
- What is he doing?
- Move.

19:49.208 --> 19:51.207
Breathe, relax.

19:51.208 --> 19:54.791
- I can't breathe.
- Stop.

19:55.041 --> 19:56.915
I can't brea...

19:56.916 --> 19:59.207
Look at me.

19:59.208 --> 20:02.625
- Relax, Brigitte.
- Breathe.

20:03.416 --> 20:07.166
- I can't! Help, I can't do it!
- Look at me, stay with me.

20:29.166 --> 20:30.375
Let's bounce.

20:36.625 --> 20:38.624
- What's going on?
- Shush.

20:38.625 --> 20:41.333
What shush? Calm down, boy.

20:45.208 --> 20:47.790
What? What's going on?

20:47.791 --> 20:50.832
- Why did you do that?
- Did you kill someone?

20:50.833 --> 20:52.665
Next time, I'll kill you.

20:52.666 --> 20:54.332
- Is that a threat?
- Yes.

20:54.333 --> 20:56.915
We're here for the money,
not to kill people.

20:56.916 --> 20:59.915
- Are you threatening me?
- Yes.

20:59.916 --> 21:02.540
I didn't kill anyone,
this thing just went off!

21:02.541 --> 21:05.749
- Calm down.
- Shut up!

21:05.750 --> 21:07.915
We're fine, nothing happened, calm down.

21:07.916 --> 21:10.041
Don't do that ever again!

21:11.458 --> 21:13.916
Shut up! Shut the fuck up!

21:27.041 --> 21:29.333
<i>- What's the story?
- He recognized Sulak from the photo.</i>

21:29.500 --> 21:31.624
Take everything. The other side, too.

21:31.625 --> 21:34.457
<i>Hello. Tell me what happened.</i>

21:34.458 --> 21:36.832
<i>She's the cashier who got attacked.</i>

21:36.833 --> 21:38.583
<i>I'll go talk to her.</i>

21:38.833 --> 21:41.040
<i>They came in, we got violently attacked.</i>

21:41.041 --> 21:44.540
<i>They pointed their guns at us,
they were shouting.</i>

21:44.541 --> 21:48.249
<i>- How many were they?
- Four or five.</i>

21:48.250 --> 21:50.832
<i>- Can you describe them?
- Yes.</i>

21:50.833 --> 21:52.707
One big Black guy.

21:52.708 --> 21:56.790
A beast with bloody eyes.

21:56.791 --> 21:59.415
And a small hysterical white guy.

21:59.416 --> 22:04.332
In my opinion... You know?
He was screaming, shouting, shooting.

22:04.333 --> 22:07.374
And a blond guy with blue eyes,
in a complete panic too.

22:07.375 --> 22:10.290
He was rude to everyone. Very rude.

22:10.291 --> 22:14.249
- And then?
- I screamed, and they all left.

22:14.250 --> 22:18.082
- And they took nothing?
- They took our takings.

22:18.083 --> 22:20.541
I can humbly say that I saved lives.

22:20.750 --> 22:22.750
That's great.

22:22.916 --> 22:26.499
So? What do you think?

22:26.500 --> 22:29.707
With dumbasses like him,
we will never catch Sulak.

22:29.708 --> 22:31.458
For sure.

22:34.583 --> 22:38.500
We're organizing having drinks tonight,
for your departure.

22:39.041 --> 22:40.916
A farewell party? I don't like that.

22:42.208 --> 22:44.165
Warm bubbly, cold appetizers.

22:44.166 --> 22:46.791
Drunk officers trying
to hook up with the receptionist.

22:47.458 --> 22:49.832
- Pathetic.
- It makes the guys happy.

22:49.833 --> 22:52.708
It's not every day you get promoted
to Chief of Organized Crime.

22:52.958 --> 22:54.375
We need to celebrate.

22:55.458 --> 22:57.416
If you say so.

22:59.041 --> 23:00.291
Ciao.

23:29.958 --> 23:31.832
- What?
- Let's get out of here.

23:31.833 --> 23:34.250
- Now?
- Pack your things.

23:36.750 --> 23:39.625
Get dressed, pack a bag,
meet me downstairs.

23:42.208 --> 23:43.625
Don't turn on the light.

23:46.458 --> 23:51.000
Drago, Marika, let's get out of here.
Take the BMW, we'll see you in Paris.

23:53.500 --> 23:56.125
Patrick! Wake up. We're leaving!

23:58.000 --> 24:01.000
- What's happening?
- He thinks the cops are coming.

24:02.083 --> 24:04.250
- Drago, move!
- Coming.

24:29.208 --> 24:30.833
Shit.

24:40.833 --> 24:44.583
It's crazy how you can feel
they're coming. How do you do that?

24:45.291 --> 24:46.958
- Fuck!
- Did you see that?

24:48.916 --> 24:51.541
- Are we going to Paris?
- Let's go, <i>mi amor.</i>

24:59.500 --> 25:03.124
I told Drago. It's over, I'm out.

25:03.125 --> 25:04.999
I've had enough of the police raids.

25:05.000 --> 25:08.957
No more prison, no more lawyers,
no more packages. Enough.

25:08.958 --> 25:11.874
I've had enough.
He promised he would stop.

25:11.875 --> 25:14.374
- Drago never went to prison?
- No.

25:14.375 --> 25:17.165
But it always ends up with prison.

25:17.166 --> 25:19.583
Who ended up in jail?

25:23.041 --> 25:24.375
My ex.

25:26.333 --> 25:27.875
He died in there.

25:29.458 --> 25:31.583
A settling of scores.

25:32.916 --> 25:34.582
What are you thinking? Banks?

25:34.583 --> 25:37.165
Banks are all connected
to local police stations.

25:37.166 --> 25:39.290
Armed security, traceable bills.

25:39.291 --> 25:40.582
Foreign exchange counters?

25:40.583 --> 25:46.249
No. You know what's good?
Fancy jewelers.

25:46.250 --> 25:49.249
Jewelry is nice, it's small, fancy.

25:49.250 --> 25:52.457
I'm a thug's girl, that's it,
That's how it is, I can't change.

25:52.458 --> 25:54.125
And you?

25:55.791 --> 25:58.833
I'm not a thug's girl, I'm with an artist.

26:00.875 --> 26:03.582
A poet, an outsider, a rebel.

26:03.583 --> 26:06.832
Everything he does, he does well.
He tried rollerblading,

26:06.833 --> 26:10.624
he was a natural. Jumps, tricks...

26:10.625 --> 26:12.707
- Backflips.
- You're addicted.

26:12.708 --> 26:14.416
We are addicted, yeah.

26:15.541 --> 26:17.832
Drago drives me crazy too.

26:17.833 --> 26:20.541
But I won't put mine on rollerblades.

26:24.541 --> 26:28.082
What are we doing with a loser like him?
He's nothing but trouble.

26:28.083 --> 26:31.207
You know, if it wasn't for the fact
he's your friend...

26:31.208 --> 26:33.041
Yes, but he's my friend.

26:34.000 --> 26:36.207
- Okay, but be careful.
- I'll talk to him.

26:36.208 --> 26:37.166
- You know what?
- What?

26:37.958 --> 26:39.250
If they go to jail...

26:39.375 --> 26:41.374
- Let's end up together.
- Sure.

26:41.375 --> 26:42.541
Deal!

26:45.083 --> 26:48.832
I don't understand, why aren't we dancing?

26:48.833 --> 26:51.000
- We're going.
- Let's go.

26:52.791 --> 26:54.708
Let's go!

27:35.000 --> 27:36.749
Hey. Tell me, Bruno.

27:36.750 --> 27:39.040
Your bling, who will you flog it to?

27:39.041 --> 27:41.290
- My bling?
- Yeah.

27:41.291 --> 27:44.958
We'll flog it back to them,
or the insurance companies.

27:45.416 --> 27:46.957
That's a good plan.

27:46.958 --> 27:49.458
That's smart, it could work.

27:50.375 --> 27:52.625
What's this idiot doing now?

27:54.416 --> 27:57.707
He's messing with a guy
he shouldn't mess with.

27:57.708 --> 27:59.124
- Do you know him?
- Yeah,

27:59.125 --> 28:00.624
Steve. He's from Yugoslavia.

28:00.625 --> 28:03.415
Go talk to him, he's gonna crush him.

28:03.416 --> 28:06.000
- I want him to get crushed.
- Go.

28:15.500 --> 28:17.750
Steve...

28:36.625 --> 28:38.457
It's paradise here.

28:38.458 --> 28:40.749
French cops are babies.

28:40.750 --> 28:44.540
French prisons are better
than hotels in Yugoslavia.

28:44.541 --> 28:46.207
It's paradise, I'm telling you.

28:46.208 --> 28:49.040
- Are you working?
- Here and there.

28:49.041 --> 28:51.749
I was Belmondo's bodyguard.

28:51.750 --> 28:53.665
Belmondo? Seriously?

28:53.666 --> 28:55.415
I even shot a movie with him.

28:55.416 --> 28:57.457
Hear that? He knows Belmondo.

28:57.458 --> 29:01.500
Belmondo, damn. That's awesome.

29:02.458 --> 29:04.916
I'm sleeping where Belmondo...

29:05.958 --> 29:09.374
Not sure you'd be into it,
but if you want to work with me,

29:09.375 --> 29:11.708
I may have something in the works.

29:12.083 --> 29:13.708
We'll see.

29:37.208 --> 29:40.290
Hello, sir. Welcome.
What can I do for you?

29:40.291 --> 29:42.250
I'd like to see your earrings.

29:42.375 --> 29:43.333
Of course, follow me.

29:47.208 --> 29:48.957
Is it for a special occasion?

29:48.958 --> 29:52.290
- An anniversary?
- Wedding anniversary.

29:52.291 --> 29:55.582
- Very well. Do you have a budget in mind?
- No, I thought...

29:55.583 --> 29:59.999
Ladies and gentlemen, this is a robbery.
Everything will be fine.

30:00.000 --> 30:02.957
I'll handle it. Your hands, please.

30:02.958 --> 30:06.208
On the floor, sir. On the floor.

30:06.458 --> 30:08.208
Your hands, please. Hands.

30:09.500 --> 30:11.416
Go. Fifty seconds.

30:13.875 --> 30:16.249
Stay calm. We're here for the jewelry.

30:16.250 --> 30:17.541
Nobody will get hurt.

30:21.291 --> 30:22.791
Stay calm, thank you.

30:22.916 --> 30:25.375
No noise. It'll soon be over.

30:30.791 --> 30:32.208
Thirty seconds.

30:37.708 --> 30:39.708
Let's go!

30:40.458 --> 30:43.457
Thank you for cooperating.
Have a lovely day.

30:43.458 --> 30:45.832
It was a pleasure doing business with you.

30:45.833 --> 30:48.083
- And have a nice weekend.
- Thanks.

30:54.916 --> 30:56.375
Great job!

30:57.000 --> 30:58.333
Let's go.

31:06.208 --> 31:09.791
- Shit, there are two cars behind us.
- Relax.

31:13.208 --> 31:15.540
- What are you doing?
- I'll handle it.

31:15.541 --> 31:17.207
Move!

31:17.208 --> 31:20.249
They think they own the place.
It's always the same.

31:20.250 --> 31:21.915
Calm down, I'll take care of it.

31:21.916 --> 31:24.583
- I'm calm, I just need to pick up my kids.
- Excuse me.

31:24.791 --> 31:28.125
Move. You're blocking traffic, sir.

31:29.041 --> 31:30.416
Stay calm.

31:31.875 --> 31:35.125
- You can go, ma'am, move.
- Thank you, officer.

31:46.833 --> 31:50.041
- I'm telling you, this bastard...
- Can I get a coffee?

31:50.916 --> 31:53.166
- He attacked me.
- Shut up!

31:54.083 --> 31:55.458
One at a time!

31:56.458 --> 31:57.750
Want me to sit down?

31:58.125 --> 31:59.958
Sit down!

32:00.250 --> 32:01.625
I'll press charges.

32:05.791 --> 32:07.750
What the hell?
We can hear you from over there.

32:08.750 --> 32:11.790
I'm the victim,
but these assholes won't listen.

32:11.791 --> 32:12.874
What did you say?

32:12.875 --> 32:15.457
Assholes... What's going on?

32:15.458 --> 32:19.708
He says his client didn't pay him.
They had a fight. Nothing new.

32:20.333 --> 32:22.416
We found this on him.

32:24.666 --> 32:27.916
Drugs, soliciting, assault, theft.

32:28.500 --> 32:30.333
That's quite the list.

32:31.875 --> 32:35.125
Get me out of here
and I'll give you a crew.

32:35.708 --> 32:38.500
A crew? Who? What crew?

32:38.833 --> 32:41.875
Yugoslavs. They're planning a robbery.
I know one of them.

32:43.625 --> 32:45.208
But... Keep going, I'm interested.

32:45.375 --> 32:47.041
Take these off me, then we'll talk.

32:47.208 --> 32:49.249
- And my complaint?
- We'll write it down.

32:49.250 --> 32:50.915
Take it. Come with me.

32:50.916 --> 32:52.666
- And I want my money.
- Don't push it.

32:54.583 --> 32:56.416
The Jaeger-LeCoultre I told you about.

32:57.458 --> 33:01.332
A platinum model
with automatic perpetual movement.

33:01.333 --> 33:03.415
Classic and modern.

33:03.416 --> 33:04.833
It's very popular.

33:06.041 --> 33:07.416
Do you like it?

33:10.666 --> 33:13.791
- Is that a yes or a no?
- Yes, I said.

33:15.416 --> 33:16.707
Could we...

33:16.708 --> 33:19.708
- Can I put it on you?
- Of course.

33:25.583 --> 33:28.125
- Isn't it a bit heavy?
- No, I don't think so.

33:28.250 --> 33:33.125
- How much is it?
- This model is 63,000 francs.

33:34.000 --> 33:37.333
I see. I better not lose it then.

33:37.916 --> 33:41.374
Or have it stolen, because these days...

33:41.375 --> 33:43.791
There are so many robberies, you know?

33:44.916 --> 33:46.875
Listen...

33:47.750 --> 33:49.124
I'll take it.

33:49.125 --> 33:52.165
- Very good. Will you keep it on?
- Yes, please.

33:52.166 --> 33:54.415
I'll let you talk to my colleague
about the payment.

33:54.416 --> 33:56.125
- Thank you.
- Thank you, sir.

34:08.250 --> 34:09.499
- Hello, sir.
- Hello.

34:09.500 --> 34:11.957
Congratulations, it's a fine piece.

34:11.958 --> 34:14.208
Thank you. Can I get a discount?

34:15.666 --> 34:18.083
I don't think that's possible.

34:21.000 --> 34:22.666
What if I pay cash?

34:24.833 --> 34:28.541
In that case, I can give you 3% off.

34:30.041 --> 34:31.208
Five.

34:35.500 --> 34:36.750
Three point five.

34:39.000 --> 34:41.875
Three point five...

34:57.583 --> 34:59.625
I'll take it.

35:07.583 --> 35:08.958
It's nice.

35:39.833 --> 35:42.666
- What time is it?
- 7:00.

35:44.375 --> 35:46.458
You always get up early.

35:48.000 --> 35:50.125
Let me sleep.

35:53.208 --> 35:56.333
- Croissants?
- Yes.

36:05.416 --> 36:08.665
- My love?
- Yes, my love?

36:08.666 --> 36:10.915
Can you get me tampons?

36:10.916 --> 36:12.583
Of course, my love.

36:13.416 --> 36:15.166
Thank you.

38:02.208 --> 38:04.750
You don't know any of these guys, right?

38:06.500 --> 38:09.916
- That's right.
- Sure.

38:11.375 --> 38:16.166
- And you? Miss...
- Braumann, Sophie. No.

38:16.291 --> 38:17.791
No, what?

38:18.583 --> 38:20.125
No, I don't know them.

38:23.291 --> 38:24.707
Sophie Braumann.

38:24.708 --> 38:27.082
That's Alsatian, Braumann.

38:27.083 --> 38:29.999
- My parents are from Bordeaux.
- Bordeaux?

38:30.000 --> 38:31.875
That's a beautiful city.

38:32.166 --> 38:34.915
The Saint-Jean neighborhood,
the Saint-André cathedral,

38:34.916 --> 38:36.875
the Garonne, the canelé cakes.

38:37.000 --> 38:41.040
- The wine, sometimes.
- Why the hell am I here?

38:41.041 --> 38:42.916
What do you think?

38:43.375 --> 38:46.832
I don't know this girl,
we hooked up last night.

38:46.833 --> 38:48.500
If I had known...

38:48.708 --> 38:50.915
It's dangerous to follow strangers.

38:50.916 --> 38:53.083
Has your mother from Bordeaux
never told you that?

38:54.125 --> 38:56.458
No, sir. She never told me that.

38:58.125 --> 38:59.707
Okay.

38:59.708 --> 39:02.958
Stop taking me for a fool, both of you.

39:03.291 --> 39:04.874
Your little act is worn out.

39:04.875 --> 39:09.791
You, honey,
I'll arrest you as an accessory.

39:10.083 --> 39:12.291
Criminal conspiracy.

39:12.416 --> 39:16.375
Fake ID, because they are fake IDs, right?

39:17.208 --> 39:21.665
And possession of stolen goods,
or do you have a receipt for the necklace?

39:21.666 --> 39:23.790
Accessory to what? Are you insane?

39:23.791 --> 39:25.708
Leave her alone.

39:26.375 --> 39:28.666
Do you know the women's wing
at La Santé prison?

39:29.916 --> 39:33.082
It's no Club Med.
especially for a pretty chick like you.

39:33.083 --> 39:35.457
She's gonna make a lot of friends. A lot.

39:35.458 --> 39:39.041
I didn't do anything,
I don't know this guy, we fucked once.

39:39.791 --> 39:42.708
I hope he was good,
because you're gonna pay for it.

39:43.750 --> 39:47.124
You're looking at five years in jail,
at least.

39:47.125 --> 39:50.165
When you're out, you'll be broken.

39:50.166 --> 39:52.082
Screwed.

39:52.083 --> 39:55.207
You won't be able to work again,
I'll make sure of that.

39:55.208 --> 39:58.124
You'll have to work the streets
to pay for your fix.

39:58.125 --> 40:00.874
One morning,
you'll end up dead in a dumpster

40:00.875 --> 40:03.582
behind a bar with a syringe in your arm.

40:03.583 --> 40:05.208
I don't do drugs.

40:07.375 --> 40:10.082
- Not yet, but it will happen.
- I didn't do anything.

40:10.083 --> 40:13.291
- The court will decide.
- Enough!

40:14.125 --> 40:15.416
Stop.

40:17.791 --> 40:20.832
- Why do you care?
- Fine, you win.

40:20.833 --> 40:22.957
Leave her alone, I'll talk.

40:22.958 --> 40:24.583
There you go.

40:28.875 --> 40:30.416
What do I get in return?

40:31.333 --> 40:33.749
I'll give you all the robberies
if you leave her alone.

40:33.750 --> 40:34.958
And your buddies?

40:36.541 --> 40:37.916
What buddies?

40:41.125 --> 40:43.582
- Pérez?
<i>- Yes, boss?</i>

40:43.583 --> 40:47.291
- Come pick up the lady.
<i>- Okay, boss. I'm on my way.</i>

40:52.833 --> 40:55.666
- Okay, come on.
- It's okay.

40:56.333 --> 40:58.290
- Ouch.
- Come on.

40:58.291 --> 41:00.250
Let's go!

41:10.916 --> 41:13.790
- What you did is really shitty.
- I know.

41:13.791 --> 41:16.125
I'm listening.

41:22.666 --> 41:26.790
Finally, the Cora supermarket in Beaune,
was that you?

41:26.791 --> 41:28.125
Yes.

41:29.041 --> 41:30.833
Tell me more.

41:32.333 --> 41:34.083
You won't arrest her, right?

41:35.083 --> 41:36.249
I gave you my word.

41:36.250 --> 41:38.915
- Yeah.
- I did.

41:38.916 --> 41:41.874
I'll talk to the judge,
she'll get probation.

41:41.875 --> 41:43.583
What about her fake IDs?

41:53.583 --> 41:55.332
What do you want to know?

41:55.333 --> 41:57.916
I went in, I robbed the place and I left.

41:58.375 --> 41:59.875
End of story.

42:01.291 --> 42:03.125
- Alone?
- Yes.

42:03.583 --> 42:08.290
You say you robbed 19 supermarkets
in eight months. Impressive.

42:08.291 --> 42:10.457
Always alone?

42:10.458 --> 42:12.874
- Always alone.
- No, I don't buy that.

42:12.875 --> 42:14.625
I'll tell you what I think.

42:15.250 --> 42:18.290
You were with your buddy Drago,
and the girl was waiting in the car.

42:18.291 --> 42:19.708
I don't know any Dragan.

42:20.500 --> 42:23.166
Dragan? We busted your buddies.

42:25.291 --> 42:27.166
Stop playing stupid, Bruno.

42:30.916 --> 42:33.082
Come on, you have enough
to make the judge hard.

42:33.083 --> 42:36.458
No, I'm very greedy,
that's my biggest flaw.

42:37.541 --> 42:39.375
Well, it's mine too.

42:40.458 --> 42:42.374
By the way, I need a favor.

42:42.375 --> 42:43.791
What is it?

42:45.458 --> 42:46.958
Can I keep my watch?

42:47.750 --> 42:51.624
Your watch? What's so special
about your Kelton?

42:51.625 --> 42:55.124
It's my dad's.
He gave it to me, it's precious to me.

42:55.125 --> 42:57.958
The guards will take it from me
if I have it when I go in.

43:00.041 --> 43:01.875
If it's a sentimental piece...

43:04.291 --> 43:05.500
Thank you.

43:11.666 --> 43:14.291
Let me say goodbye, please.

43:14.458 --> 43:15.958
Be quick.

43:17.625 --> 43:19.125
My love.

43:26.333 --> 43:28.333
I love you.

43:29.791 --> 43:31.999
- Come with me.
- I'll wait for you.

43:32.000 --> 43:33.082
I love you.

43:33.083 --> 43:36.083
Let's go, lovebirds.

45:02.500 --> 45:03.833
Hi.

45:06.083 --> 45:07.375
Hi.

45:13.041 --> 45:14.541
What are you in for?

45:15.583 --> 45:18.666
- Miscarriage of justice. You?
- Same.

45:31.500 --> 45:33.375
I got 12 years for armed robbery.

45:36.708 --> 45:38.083
You?

45:40.833 --> 45:42.500
Awaiting trial.

45:46.375 --> 45:48.040
I don't like the decor in here.

45:48.041 --> 45:50.124
And the food looks disgusting.

45:50.125 --> 45:51.791
I don't plan on staying.

45:54.083 --> 45:55.916
Jean-Loup Lablache.

45:56.958 --> 45:58.665
Bruno Sulak.

45:58.666 --> 46:00.083
I know.

46:35.916 --> 46:38.000
I don't think guards make enough money.

46:40.625 --> 46:42.625
I could have something for you.

46:43.833 --> 46:46.957
I could be interested.
But not here. Move.

46:46.958 --> 46:48.458
You know where to find me.

47:22.625 --> 47:26.040
<i>My love, every day, with my words,</i>

47:26.041 --> 47:28.125
<i>I caress your skin with the tip of my pen.</i>

47:29.250 --> 47:31.083
<i>And your lips too.</i>

47:31.791 --> 47:33.707
<i>You know,</i>

47:33.708 --> 47:35.415
<i>they want to make a beast out of me,</i>

47:35.416 --> 47:39.040
<i>but no matter how much they try
with force or ruse,</i>

47:39.041 --> 47:40.708
<i>I won't give in.</i>

47:41.208 --> 47:44.249
<i>I want to live the life I want,
to stay the boy that is exhilarated,</i>

47:44.250 --> 47:47.165
<i>like in the Reggiani song
that you like so much.</i>

47:47.166 --> 47:50.833
<i>To stay the person who is amazed,
who dreams, who is waiting for you.</i>

47:52.166 --> 47:55.416
<i>Life, my love, is not eternal.</i>

47:59.666 --> 48:01.915
<i>I'm alive, alive when I write to you,</i>

48:01.916 --> 48:05.458
<i>when I smell sometimes
the wind brushing my skin.</i>

48:09.666 --> 48:12.374
- How do we do it?
- Seventy-one.

48:12.375 --> 48:13.708
Okay.

48:15.041 --> 48:18.833
Hands on the table, old hand.

48:22.791 --> 48:24.874
That's nice. I like it.

48:24.875 --> 48:26.582
That's good stuff.

48:26.583 --> 48:28.040
We can make a trident with this.

48:28.041 --> 48:30.707
Tie them together, it'll hold.
It's strong.

48:30.708 --> 48:33.415
- Will you get more?
- Of course I will.

48:33.416 --> 48:34.958
<i>You were right,</i>

48:35.083 --> 48:38.207
<i>I like being an outsider,
different, like an artist.</i>

48:38.208 --> 48:40.790
<i>In another life,
I could have been a painter or a writer.</i>

48:40.791 --> 48:42.957
<i>But here, in prison,</i>

48:42.958 --> 48:44.582
<i>there's no room for culture.</i>

48:44.583 --> 48:47.000
<i>We are misunderstood, abandoned.</i>

48:47.291 --> 48:51.291
<i>They won't get to me, I don't want
to fall into hatred and violence.</i>

48:51.875 --> 48:53.708
<i>I'm stronger than this</i>

48:54.541 --> 48:56.791
<i>and I'll be back more alive than ever.</i>

48:58.833 --> 49:01.916
I got 12 years in the slammer,
I've done nearly six now.

49:02.708 --> 49:05.750
When I get out, I think...

49:06.666 --> 49:08.166
<i>I'll do simple things.</i>

49:09.000 --> 49:12.250
<i>Chowing down by the sea.
Maybe in the mountains?</i>

49:12.500 --> 49:15.666
I'm not saying
that I'll shack up with a goat.

50:07.250 --> 50:08.416
All clear.

50:54.125 --> 50:57.541
Wait. It's holding. No, wait.

51:05.875 --> 51:09.833
Come on.

51:11.375 --> 51:12.750
Come on.

51:16.208 --> 51:18.416
Let me... Shit.

51:37.666 --> 51:39.999
Yes! That's it.

51:40.000 --> 51:41.665
Let's go!

51:41.666 --> 51:43.833
- Come on.
- Slowly.

52:17.916 --> 52:19.332
Jump!

52:19.333 --> 52:21.165
Come on, Jean-Loup!

52:21.166 --> 52:22.375
Come on!

52:24.541 --> 52:26.583
Come on, you're almost there.

52:26.708 --> 52:29.249
Come on, you're almost there.

52:29.250 --> 52:32.540
Give me your hand.
Come on, Jean-Loup.

52:32.541 --> 52:35.999
You're almost there, Jean-Loup,
take my hand. Come on.

52:36.000 --> 52:38.000
Good, hurry up.

52:41.791 --> 52:45.374
- Come on, Jean-Loup!
- I won't make it.

52:45.375 --> 52:47.375
- Come on!
