57:04.833 --> 57:06.583
A lighter?

57:30.291 --> 57:32.332
Flat whites are not good for digestion.

57:32.333 --> 57:33.749
What do you want?

57:33.750 --> 57:35.625
Nothing. We thought we'd have
breakfast with you.

57:36.333 --> 57:38.375
That's nice.
Were you in the neighborhood?

57:40.458 --> 57:42.666
You know,
every cop in the country is after you.

57:43.708 --> 57:46.624
We'll bust you,
in a week, a month, a year.

57:46.625 --> 57:48.124
We'll see about that, pal.

57:48.125 --> 57:49.457
Why did you come here?

57:49.458 --> 57:53.125
To tell you to back off.
Don't you have other guys to catch?

57:55.916 --> 57:57.083
You're my favorite.

57:59.833 --> 58:01.000
You're mine too.

58:04.458 --> 58:05.958
Mine too.

58:06.333 --> 58:07.624
Thank you.

58:07.625 --> 58:10.125
- Have a nice day.
- Anytime.

58:21.416 --> 58:24.375
- This is a bit mad, right?
- A bit.

58:25.750 --> 58:28.375
Let's go. Come on.

59:00.875 --> 59:02.415
- Hello.
- Hello.

59:02.416 --> 59:03.915
- Delostane.
- Go ahead.

59:03.916 --> 59:05.041
Thank you.

59:09.458 --> 59:11.874
- Hello, sir.
- Hello.

59:11.875 --> 59:15.791
Come in, step to the side.
Raise your arms.

59:20.041 --> 59:22.832
Don't move.

59:22.833 --> 59:24.333
On the ground.

59:26.625 --> 59:29.666
- Open the door. Now.
- Open it.

59:30.166 --> 59:32.415
- Open it!
- Don't move.

59:32.416 --> 59:36.208
Go over to your friend,
lie down on the floor next to him.

59:36.916 --> 59:40.583
There. On the floor.

59:41.291 --> 59:42.666
Hello, gentlemen.

59:43.083 --> 59:46.750
First, let my friend in.

59:47.416 --> 59:49.874
- Done.
- Done?

59:49.875 --> 59:51.083
Good job.

59:54.916 --> 59:56.999
Cuff yourselves to the heater.

59:57.000 --> 59:59.249
I want the key to the cell.

59:59.250 --> 01:00:02.332
Jean-Loup Lablache's.

01:00:02.333 --> 01:00:04.291
- Now.
- Thank you.

01:00:06.250 --> 01:00:08.749
Michel, how was your daughter's recital?

01:00:08.750 --> 01:00:10.415
Very good, thank you.

01:00:10.416 --> 01:00:13.791
- Number 12.
- Number 12.

01:00:15.000 --> 01:00:16.125
Sit down.

01:00:19.416 --> 01:00:21.583
Cuff yourselves.

01:00:22.375 --> 01:00:23.541
Gate!

01:00:24.000 --> 01:00:25.875
Gate. Open the gate.

01:00:28.458 --> 01:00:29.707
Good.

01:00:29.708 --> 01:00:30.875
Gate.

01:00:45.666 --> 01:00:47.791
- What do you smoke?
- Gauloises.

01:00:48.416 --> 01:00:50.290
- Not very strong.
- Unfiltered.

01:00:50.291 --> 01:00:51.500
I thought it was stronger.

01:01:04.750 --> 01:01:06.791
You're crazy.

01:01:07.708 --> 01:01:10.375
- You're amazing.
- I told you I'd be back.

01:01:15.791 --> 01:01:17.165
My friends are back.

01:01:17.166 --> 01:01:19.707
- Bye, guys.
- Goodbye, gentlemen.

01:01:19.708 --> 01:01:21.707
- It was a pleasure.
- Thank you.

01:01:21.708 --> 01:01:23.250
- Bye.
- Have a nice day.

01:01:23.375 --> 01:01:24.832
- See you.
- See you.

01:01:24.833 --> 01:01:26.750
Bastards.

01:01:27.708 --> 01:01:29.208
Fuck!

01:01:31.333 --> 01:01:32.958
Those guys have some balls.

01:01:36.875 --> 01:01:37.708
Goodbye.

01:01:50.000 --> 01:01:51.916
You guys are insane.

01:01:54.625 --> 01:01:56.707
ID, cash, you've got everything.

01:01:56.708 --> 01:01:59.332
And a ticket to Rio, through Lisbon.

01:01:59.333 --> 01:02:01.166
Your name is Carlos.

01:02:01.958 --> 01:02:04.124
Stop it, guys, I'm gonna cry!

01:02:04.125 --> 01:02:06.750
- We'll be there soon.
- Thank you.

01:02:25.458 --> 01:02:27.583
- Room 14, second floor.
- Thank you.

01:02:44.375 --> 01:02:45.791
The door!

01:02:58.166 --> 01:02:59.791
I love you.

01:03:07.875 --> 01:03:10.958
- What are you watching?
- A sad movie.

01:03:11.875 --> 01:03:15.541
Hello? Can I speak to Franchet?
It's a private matter.

01:03:18.333 --> 01:03:20.708
- Is it good?
- It's sad. I like it.

01:03:23.541 --> 01:03:26.874
Franchet, it's me.
I've got the rocks. Yes.

01:03:26.875 --> 01:03:28.583
Twenty-five million.

01:03:29.500 --> 01:03:31.625
In new francs, it's at least 100k.

01:03:32.541 --> 01:03:33.875
Yes.

01:03:35.250 --> 01:03:37.458
Tomorrow, midday. Pompidou Centre.

01:03:38.541 --> 01:03:39.833
Okay, let's do that.

01:03:41.916 --> 01:03:44.333
Come into my arms, my love.
It's too sad.

01:03:48.833 --> 01:03:51.041
We got a lead. You'll like this.

01:03:52.083 --> 01:03:54.540
Only one man. Where is the location
for the exchange?

01:03:54.541 --> 01:03:56.958
- Franchet, the insurer.
- Yeah, at Beaubourg.

01:03:57.083 --> 01:03:58.999
- Beaubourg.
- Pompidou Centre?

01:03:59.000 --> 01:04:00.415
- When?
- Twelve o'clock.

01:04:00.416 --> 01:04:02.166
- Twelve.
- Yeah.

01:04:12.458 --> 01:04:13.958
- Circular motion, I said.
- Yes.

01:06:03.000 --> 01:06:04.458
Quiet, please.

01:06:04.791 --> 01:06:06.540
The court is now in session.

01:06:06.541 --> 01:06:08.625
Will the defendant rise, please.

01:06:10.708 --> 01:06:14.999
Your name is Sulak Bruno, born
November 6th, 1955, in Sidi Bel Abbès.

01:06:15.000 --> 01:06:16.915
Yugoslavian nationality.

01:06:16.916 --> 01:06:19.583
I'm not Yugoslavian,
I'm French, Your Honor.

01:06:19.708 --> 01:06:23.000
My father is French from Poland,
like Michel Poniatowski,

01:06:23.125 --> 01:06:25.708
and my mother is a <i>pied-noir,</i>
like Marthe Villalonga.

01:06:26.166 --> 01:06:29.415
Quiet, please. Good.

01:06:29.416 --> 01:06:33.582
You are being charged for
fraudulently taking away cash

01:06:33.583 --> 01:06:37.624
to the detriment of supermarkets,
Mammouth, Atac and Rallye,

01:06:37.625 --> 01:06:39.374
between July 6th and 20th, 1983.

01:06:39.375 --> 01:06:43.040
These acts were committed
as a part of a group,

01:06:43.041 --> 01:06:45.707
and with use of a weapon
or threat thereof.

01:06:45.708 --> 01:06:48.540
As well as criminal conspiracy.

01:06:48.541 --> 01:06:52.915
Before we hear the testimony
of the lead investigator,

01:06:52.916 --> 01:06:55.415
do you have anything to say?

01:06:55.416 --> 01:06:56.957
I do, Your Honor.

01:06:56.958 --> 01:06:58.957
You may speak.

01:06:58.958 --> 01:07:02.624
You know,
I was an excellent soldier. Excellent.

01:07:02.625 --> 01:07:04.707
And I became an excellent outcast,

01:07:04.708 --> 01:07:08.290
just as I could I have become
an excellent cop or magistrate.

01:07:08.291 --> 01:07:09.624
I surely doubt it.

01:07:09.625 --> 01:07:14.124
What I would like for you to understand,
ladies and gentlemen of the jury,

01:07:14.125 --> 01:07:18.415
and to you too,
Mr. Self-Righteous Prosecutor,

01:07:18.416 --> 01:07:21.165
is that I don't recognize your court
or your justice.

01:07:21.166 --> 01:07:24.291
You mean nothing to me,
I deny you the right to judge me.

01:07:24.416 --> 01:07:25.666
The court takes note of this.

01:07:25.791 --> 01:07:29.790
And neither Annie, Patrick nor Drago
were ever my accomplices.

01:07:29.791 --> 01:07:32.333
That is not what the investigation
brought proof of.

01:07:32.458 --> 01:07:36.208
Just like in astrology,
the police can say whatever they want.

01:07:37.333 --> 01:07:38.708
Enough.

01:07:39.166 --> 01:07:41.874
Sulak, we won't tolerate your impudence.

01:07:41.875 --> 01:07:44.332
Impudence is all I have left.

01:07:44.333 --> 01:07:46.166
Fine, sit down.

01:07:51.625 --> 01:07:53.750
Defendant Drago, please rise.

01:07:54.458 --> 01:07:56.833
He's not a proper Yugoslavian either.

01:08:03.416 --> 01:08:05.458
Will the defendants please rise?

01:08:07.541 --> 01:08:10.582
After due consideration,
the court and the jury

01:08:10.583 --> 01:08:13.708
sentence each of you
to three years in prison.

01:08:15.041 --> 01:08:18.332
As for yourself, madam,
since there were no previous convictions,

01:08:18.333 --> 01:08:21.624
you are sentenced to 18 months in prison,

01:08:21.625 --> 01:08:25.957
which will be suspended
and served on probation.

01:08:25.958 --> 01:08:28.749
You will be subjected to strict controls

01:08:28.750 --> 01:08:31.040
for a period of two years.

01:08:31.041 --> 01:08:34.249
I'd like to say one more thing.

01:08:34.250 --> 01:08:38.707
Mr. Sulak, before you continue
your tour of France's court system

01:08:38.708 --> 01:08:41.124
for your many other offenses,

01:08:41.125 --> 01:08:44.165
please know that
if you don't change your attitude,

01:08:44.166 --> 01:08:47.540
the sentences will be extremely serious.

01:08:47.541 --> 01:08:49.541
Court is adjourned.

01:09:23.083 --> 01:09:24.208
Pick a card.

01:09:25.500 --> 01:09:27.666
Do you really think
that you'd have been a good cop?

01:09:28.458 --> 01:09:30.041
Of course I do.

01:09:30.916 --> 01:09:33.374
Finally, the card

01:09:33.375 --> 01:09:35.291
I was waiting two rounds for.

01:09:36.625 --> 01:09:38.457
Why did you desert the legion?

01:09:38.458 --> 01:09:40.082
Long story.

01:09:40.083 --> 01:09:42.624
To validate my freefall world record,

01:09:42.625 --> 01:09:44.582
I had to sign up for another five years.

01:09:44.583 --> 01:09:46.415
Five years.

01:09:46.416 --> 01:09:49.040
Why didn't you do it?
You seemed happy.

01:09:49.041 --> 01:09:50.790
You don't understand.

01:09:50.791 --> 01:09:54.500
No one tells me what to do.
No one. Ever.

01:09:56.708 --> 01:09:57.958
Pick a card.

01:09:58.416 --> 01:10:00.707
No one tells me what to do either.

01:10:00.708 --> 01:10:02.458
No one. Ever.

01:10:05.500 --> 01:10:07.665
That's stupid, we could have been pals.

01:10:07.666 --> 01:10:10.124
I could have shown you the ropes.

01:10:10.125 --> 01:10:12.416
- The ropes?
- Of life.

01:10:13.000 --> 01:10:15.957
- Life?
- Yes, your life is too restricted,

01:10:15.958 --> 01:10:18.207
you're caught
between your bosses and felons.

01:10:18.208 --> 01:10:20.165
I am free.

01:10:20.166 --> 01:10:21.666
Really, you're free?

01:10:22.916 --> 01:10:24.250
You're really free.

01:10:26.583 --> 01:10:28.499
Do you think
you're the only adventurer here?

01:10:28.500 --> 01:10:32.333
We live the adventure too,
on the other side.

01:10:32.541 --> 01:10:35.416
You, you're either on the run
or in the clink.

01:10:36.000 --> 01:10:37.500
What kind of freedom is that?

01:10:39.791 --> 01:10:41.833
But you see, I chose this life.

01:10:42.708 --> 01:10:44.582
Even in jail, I'm freer than you.

01:10:44.583 --> 01:10:48.165
Sure. Here we go, three sixes.

01:10:48.166 --> 01:10:49.957
- Shit.
- Discard.

01:10:49.958 --> 01:10:51.916
You're a lucky bastard, seriously.

01:11:05.083 --> 01:11:07.415
Why did you go back for Jean-Loup?

01:11:07.416 --> 01:11:12.499
I promised him. And I'm a nice guy.

01:11:12.500 --> 01:11:14.540
You are a nice guy.

01:11:14.541 --> 01:11:16.832
- Of course.
- We both know that.

01:11:16.833 --> 01:11:19.582
The nicer you are,
the more people like you.

01:11:19.583 --> 01:11:21.707
The more they like you,
the more famous you get.

01:11:21.708 --> 01:11:23.666
And the more popular you get.

01:11:24.708 --> 01:11:26.583
The more you annoy people.

01:11:28.833 --> 01:11:29.958
Pick a card.

01:11:39.500 --> 01:11:40.833
Excuse me.

01:11:42.583 --> 01:11:44.457
The gun.

01:11:44.458 --> 01:11:46.000
In my bag.

01:11:48.458 --> 01:11:49.541
Follow me.

01:11:50.375 --> 01:11:54.040
Get in and shut up.

01:11:54.041 --> 01:11:56.083
Close the door. I'm watching you.

01:11:58.791 --> 01:12:03.375
So you want to play, right?
Take that! Rummy.

01:12:04.583 --> 01:12:06.707
Didn't see that coming, right?

01:12:06.708 --> 01:12:09.332
Moréas, are you sleepy?

01:12:09.333 --> 01:12:11.666
You're a humble guy.

01:12:13.208 --> 01:12:15.666
You want to play.
I don't want to play, I want to win.

01:12:16.833 --> 01:12:18.750
Hello. Don't move, guys.

01:12:21.083 --> 01:12:24.040
- Let's go.
- No, thanks.

01:12:24.041 --> 01:12:25.374
I'd love that.

01:12:25.375 --> 01:12:28.333
Guns in the bag, and the handcuff key.

01:12:28.708 --> 01:12:29.666
Now.

01:12:29.791 --> 01:12:32.791
- Let me keep mine, it means a lot.
- In that case...

01:12:37.500 --> 01:12:38.749
Are you sure?

01:12:38.750 --> 01:12:41.583
I'm too old to be on the run.
Good luck.

01:12:45.208 --> 01:12:47.041
- Bye.
- Bye.

01:12:48.125 --> 01:12:49.458
Have a nice day.

01:12:53.166 --> 01:12:54.875
Can you drop me off?

01:13:22.708 --> 01:13:25.082
<i>Spectacular escape</i>

01:13:25.083 --> 01:13:28.207
<i>in the Corail train from Montpellier
